Not ALL Vendors feel that way! We test our machines and yes - I furlowed my
eyebrows at the introduction of no parity on Simms. However APPLE has been
marketing the MAC and SI and all of it's line-up for several years and I don't
believe their archtechture to be superior from the PC. Still, we are concerned
even though we rarely find a BAD simm module. OUr concerne is more with the Compatibility
and timming sensitive problems that cn occur with some Simm on various motherboards.
What we do is this. Run the Memory tests on the newly assembled PC's and use a HOT room
for 48hrs - temperature at a constant 9o F. Then we don't stop there.. we install
software that we KNOW runs from a MATSER volume - ie. Windows - Games - and
acually run the programs for another 24 hrs. Afterall you wouldnt buy a car without first
putting gas in it and turning the KEY ... would you?


